a.title: name varchar(256) Property name (or should we put qualified names here? E.g. core:relativeToWater or core:lod2Solid)
index_number integer Index number (if multiple properties with the same name are stored and the order should be preserved)
datatype varchar the datatype should be given as a qualified datatype name from the CityGML schema (e.g. gml:GenericName, gml:DateTime)
data_valtype integer tells in which attribute(s) the value is actually stored (0=val_int, 1=val_double, 2=val_string, 3=val_date, etc.)
val_surface_geometry bigint Foreign key to SURFACE_GEOMETRY(id)
val_implicitgeom_id bigint Foreign key to IMPLICIT_GEOMETRY(id)
val_implicitgeom_refpoint geometry base point in 3D world coordinates for the instantiation of the implicit geometry
val_implicitgeom_transform varchar(1000) 4x4 transformation matrix encoded as a string of space separated double values (as strings) in row major sequence
val_grid_coverage bigint Foreign key to GRID_COVERAGE(id)
val_appearance bigint Foreign key to APPEARANCE(id)
val_dynamizer bigint Foreign key to APPEARANCE(id)
val_feature bigint Foreign key to FEATURE(id)
val_feature_is_xlink integer 0=related feature was represented inline, 1=related feature was referenced using an XLink
val_code varchar(256) if a code from a codelist should be stored, we could also put the code in the val_string attribute and omit this attribute
val_codelist integer Foreign key to CODELIST(code) (or alternatively - if we do not store codelists also in the 3DCityDB - then a URL to the codelist)
val_uom varchar unit of measure (for all subtypes of gml:Measure); the value is stored in val_double
val_complex json stores all data of complex datatypes as a JSON string (e.g. con:Height)
